content: Here are three dating jokes I came up with: "I've been on so many dates, I've started to think my OkCupid profile should just say 'I'm not a serial killer, but I do have a lot of free time.'"; "Why do dating apps make you choose a job title? Like, what's the right answer to that? 'Unemployed, but I have a nice smile'?"; and "I went on a date with a guy who said he was a 'free spirit.' I think that's just code for 'I'm unemployed and living in my parents' basement'."
